<plot>80% of clothes made in Australia are made by women and their families sewing at home and in sweatshops by "outworkers". Wages average between $2-$5 per hour. Deadline demands require 12-18 hour days. Made In Australia depicts a rarely seen strata of society and asks that Australian Made mean fairly paid.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?350895</url></doc>
